his incident to specific agents and related data, ensuring a concrete starting point for the governance dashboard. It includes relevant details like scope, severity, and compliance information.\n\n\n**Defining Incident Properties**\n\nI'm now deep-diving into defining incident properties. I've formulated a detailed incident object with properties like `title`, `scopeType`, `severity`, `owner`, and `complianceRule`. I'm populating this with real data points, building a structured representation of the incidents within the governance dashboard, and using mock-up values. It should be a strong start!\n\n\n**Detailing Incident Data**\n\nI've just added a specific incident, \"Unsigned API Administration Tunnel Call.\" This includes details like scope, severity, owner, and logs. I'm using real-world-ish data to provide a concrete example within the governance dashboard, including timestamps and a compliance rule. I'm keen to make the data compelling.\n\n\n**Populating Incident Data**\n\nI've just added \"Hardware Root HSM Certificate Rollover Warning\" to the incident data. I've populated the incident with properties like scope, severity, owner, reviewer, status, due date, description, timestamp, compliance rule, hash and logs. This specific incident is tied to a client named \"Federal Treasury Division\". I believe this data provides a helpful starting point to refine the user interface.\n\n\n**Adding Incident Data**\n\nI've just added a new incident: \"Deep Inference Drift on MED-CLINIC-H9.\" I've populated this with realistic-looking data, like scope, severity, owner, reviewer, status, due date, description, timestamp, compliance rule, hash, and logs, using a client of \"Global Retail Enclave.\" I'm confident that this data will enhance the user interface, and that this data is going to create a helpful starting point for the new dashboard.\n\n\n**Designing Visual Enhancements**\n\nI've just added \"Synchronization Time Offset Warning\". The data, including owner \"Marc