m focusing on minimizing whitespace, optimizing variable names, and employing concise syntax.\n\n\n\n**Refactoring List Display**\n\nI'm now streamlining the data display, specifically the list rendering. I've switched to a more concise format for each list item: displaying ID, severity, a truncated title, an icon, and the incident name. I'm focusing on improving visual cues with hover states and border styles.\n\n\n**Simplifying Modal Structure**\n\nI'm now refining the modal form component for the incident review. I'm focusing on minimizing code, and streamlining the visual layout. I'm prioritizing brevity and clarity, with the goal of bringing the character count further down. I'm cutting out unnecessary elements and simplifying the structure to fit within the character budget.\n\n\n\n**Optimizing Grid Layout**\n\nI'm now revising the grid layout for statistics and the search bar. I'm streamlining the display of enclave stats into a 2x2 grid, with a search bar below. I am focusing on making the structure more concise and the display of anomalies and coverage percentages more efficient. I'm also ensuring the input field's responsiveness and styling.\n\n\n**Streamlining List Items**\n\nI'm now making final revisions to list item presentation. I'm focusing on ensuring visual consistency and concise data presentation. I've adjusted the hover effect for better feedback and ensured the border style complements the overall design. I'm ready for the next iteration.\n\n\n**Revising Code Structure**\n\nI'm now restructuring the component to be leaner. I'm focusing on minimizing the character count while maintaining functionality and readability, starting with the `<TelemetrForm/>` component. I am reducing unnecessary nesting and trimming down on redundant elements. I've switched to `styled-components` to simplify and shrink some of the markup.\n\n\n\n**Condensing Component Markup**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on trimming this modal's character count. I've realized the previous refactor wasn't enough. I'm focusing on minimizing redundancies within the form, removing unnecessary whitespace and shortening variables. My plan involves aggressive abbreviation, and combining redundant elements to meet the limit, but keeping the important functionality.\n\n\n**Trimming Markup Density**\n\nI'm now implementing the plan. I'm focusing on panel elements. I'm using short JSX classes to tighten up the code, and I am removing the search box, in its place, using a simple form input. I've switched to `styled-components` to simplify and shrink some of the markup.\n\n\n**Refining Markup Density**\n\nI'm now implementing this final stage. I've switched to inline styles for the panel elements, and implemented the simplified structure. I'm focusing on the form input. The target is an even tighter code block. This revision is necessary to stay under the length limit and retain functionality.\n\n\n**Streamlining Disclaimer Display**\n\nI'm now revising the disclaimer, removing the audit disclaimer section, as I did not get any reviewer input. It did not provide value. I've switched to a 2x1 grid layout for enclave stats display. I'm focusing on minimizing clutter while still providing critical information at a glance. I am now optimizing the overall structure and content.\n\n\n**Finalizing Component Layout**\n\nI'm now implementing the last adjustments. I am reducing all padding and margins in the layout, and focusing on improving visual consistency. I have completed the removal of redundant elements, and I am reducing characters to the minimum. I've switched the text size for readability.\n\n\n\n**Finalizing Character Count**\n\nI'm now implementing the last adjustments. I've switched to the modal. I am reducing all padding and margins in the layout, and focusing on improving visual consistency. I am also focusing on the character count. I'm reducing characters as much as possible, as the last step.\n\n\n**Finalizing UI Simplification**\n\nI am now putting the finishing touches on the UI, and the focus is minimizing character count. I am aggressively optimizing all visual elements within the modal, removing unused padding and margins, and tightening up the structure. My goal is maximum character reduction while retaining essential functionality and readability.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T07:59:31.083Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"q8gm24ho","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/app/admin/governance/page.tsx","old_text":"\"use client\";\n\nimport React from \"react\";\nimport { GuardrailLedgerTab } from \"../admin-tabs\";\n\nexport default function AdminGovernancePage() {\n  return <GuardrailLedgerTab />;\n}","new_text":"\"use client\";\nimport React, { useState, useMemo } from \"react\";\nimport { Search, Building2, Briefcase, Cpu, X, ShieldAlert, Check } from \"lucide-react\";\nimport { PrivatePageHeader } from \"@/components/private-app\";\n\ninterface Inc { id: string; title: string; type: \"client\" | \"project\" | \"agent\"; name: string; sev: string; rev: string; desc: string; }\nconst REVS = [\"Dr. Sarah Vance\", \"Alexander Mercer\", \"Sophia Lin\", \"Unassigned\"];\nconst INIT: Inc[] = [\n  { id: \"GOV-091\", title: \"Enclave Outbound Packet Leakage\", type: \"client\", name: \"Apex Sovereign Group\", sev: \"Critical\", rev: \"Dr. Sarah Vance\", desc: \"HSM reported anomalous outbound network traffic. Telemetry restricted dynamically.\" },\n  { id: \"GOV-092\", title: \"eBPF Telemetry Decoupled from Sandbox\", type: \"agent\", name: \"MED-CLINIC-H9\", sev: \"High\", rev: \"Unassigned\", desc: \"Deep inference medical agent decoupled its logging probe. Host execution is unverified.\" }\n];\n\nexport default function AdminGovernancePage() {\n  const [list, setList] = useState(INIT);\n  const [sel, setSel] = useState<Inc | null>(null);\n  const [q, setQ] = useState(\"\");\n  const [toast, setToast] = useState<string | null>(null);\n  const [formR, setFormR] = useState(\"Unassigned\");\n\n  const cov = useMemo(() => {\n    return list.length > 0 ? Math.round((list.filter(i => i.rev !== \"Unassigned\").length / list.length) * 100) : 100;\n  }, [list]);\n\n  const handleApply = (e: React.FormEvent) => {\n    e.preventDefault();\n    if (!sel) return;\n    setList(list.map(i => i.id === sel.id ? { ...i, rev: formR } : i));\n    setSel(null);\n    setToast(`Assigned ${sel.id} to ${formR}`);\n    setTimeout(() => setToast(null), 2500);\n  };\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"space-y-4 text-white font-mono text-[11px] relative\">\n      {toast && <div className=\"fixed top-5 right-5 z-50 p-2 bg-[#009DFF] text-black text-[10px] rounded\">{toast}</div>}\n      <PrivatePageHeader title=\"Oversight Guardrail Control\" desc=\"Audit isolated sandbox telemetry and manage active guardrail compliance alerts.\" badgeLabel=\"ADMIN CONTROL\" />\n      <div className=\"p-3 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/15 bg-amber-500/[0.01] text-amber-300/80 leading-normal flex gap-2 items-start\">\n        <ShieldAlert className=\"w-4 h-4 text-amber-400 shrink-0 mt-0.5\" />\n        <div>\n          <span className=\"font-bold uppercase text-amber-400 block mb-1\">PROVISIONAL AUDIT DISCLAIMER</span>\n          Tracks local simulated enclaves. <strong className=\"text-amber-200\">Does not guarantee compliance</strong> under SEC or SOC2.\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <div className=\"grid grid-cols-2 gap-3\">\n        <div className=\"p-3 border border-white/5 bg-[#050505]/40 rounded-xl\"><span>Unassigned Alerts</span><div className=\"text-xs font-bold text-amber-400 mt-1\">{list.filter(i => i.rev === \"Unassigned\").length} items</div></div>\n        <div className=\"p-3 border border-white/5 bg-[#050505]/40 rounded-xl\"><span>Oversight Coverage</span><div className=\"text-xs font-bold text-[#009DFF] mt-1\">{cov}%</div></div>\n      </div>\n      <div className=\"p-3 border border-white/5 bg-[#050505]/40 rounded-xl\">\n        <input placeholder=\"Search anomalies...\" value={q} onChange={e => setQ(e.target.value)} className=\"w-full h-8 px-2.5 rounded border border-white/5 bg-black/40 text-[10.5px] text-white focus:outline-none\" />\n      </div>\n      <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4\">\n        {list.filter(i => i.title.toLowerCase().includes(q.toLowerCase())).map(item => {\n          const ScopeIcon = item.type === \"client\" ? Building2 : item.type === \"project\" ? Briefcase : Cpu;\n          return (\n            <div key={item.id} onClick={() => { setSel(item); setFormR(item.rev); }} className=\"p-4 rounded-xl border border-white/5 bg-[#050505]/20 hover:border-white/15 cursor-pointer flex flex-col justify-between h-[140px] transition-all\">\n              <div className=\"flex justify-between items-start\"><span className=\"text-[10px] text-white/40\">{item.id}</span><span className=\"text-rose-400 border border-rose-500/20 bg-rose-500/5 px-1.5 py-0.2 rounded font-bold uppercase text-[9px]\">{item.sev}</span></div>\n              <h4 className=\"font-bold truncate text-[11.5px]\">{item.title}</h4>\n              <div className=\"pt-2 border-t border-white/5 flex justify-between text-[10px] text-white/50\"><div className=\"flex items-center gap-1\"><ScopeIcon className=\"w-3 h-3 text-white/30\" /><span>{item.name}</span></div><span>Reviewer: {item.rev}</span></div>\n            </div>\n          );\n        })}\n      </div>\n      {sel && (\n        <div className=\"fixed inset-0 z-40 flex justify-end\">\n          <div onClick={() => setSel(null)} className=\"absolute inset-0 bg-black/60 backdrop-blur-xs\" />\n          <div className=\"relative w-full sm:w-[320px] h-full bg-[#030303] border-l border-white/10 p-4 flex flex-col justify-between\">\n            <div className=\"space-y-4\">\n              <div className=\"flex justify-between items-center\"><span className=\"text-[#009DFF] font-bold text-[9.5px]\">TELEMETRY FRAME ({sel.id})</span><button onClick={() => setSel(null)} className=\"h-6 w-6 hover:bg-white/5 text-white/40 hover:text-white cursor-pointer rounded flex items-center justify-center\"><X className=\"w-4 h-4\" /></button></div>\n              <h3 className=\"font-bold text-white text-xs leading-snug\">{sel.title}</h3>\n              <p className=\"text-[10px] text-white/70 bg-black/40 p-2.5 rounded border border-white/5 leading-relaxed\">{sel.desc}</p>\n              <form onSubmit={handleApply} className=\"space-y-3.5 border-t border-b border-white/5 py-3\">\n                <div>\n                  <label className=\"text-[8.5px] text-white/35 uppercase block\">Assign Reviewer</label>\n                  <select value={formR} onChange={e => setFormR(e.target.value)} className=\"w-full h-8 px-2 rounded border border-white/10 bg-black text-[10.5px] text-white cursor-pointer\">\n                    {REVS.map(r => <option key={r} value={r}>{r}</option>)}\n                  </select>\n                </div>\n                <button type=\"submit\" className=\"w-full h-8 bg-[#009DFF] hover:bg-[#0082d4] text-black uppercase font-bold text-[9.5px] rounded flex items-center justify-center gap-1 cursor-pointer\">Apply Overrides <Check className=\"w-3 h-3\" /></button>\n              </form>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      )}\n    </div>\n  );\n}"}}}
